## Endpoints Reference

### `POST /api/favorites/:propertyId` — Toggle ⭐
The main action button. One endpoint, one handler — the server decides add or remove.

```
// First press → saves it
POST /api/favorites/684abc123...
→ 201  { "success": true, "saved": true, "message": "Property added to favorites." }

// Second press → removes it
POST /api/favorites/684abc123...
→ 200  { "success": true, "saved": false, "message": "Property removed from favorites." }
```

### `GET /api/favorites` — My Saved Listings
Returns paginated favorites with full property details nested inside.

```
GET /api/favorites?page=1&limit=12
→ 200 {
  "success": true,
  "count": 2,
  "total": 2,
  "totalPages": 1,
  "currentPage": 1,
  "data": [
    {
      "_id": "...",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-09T...",
      "property": {
        "title": "Modern 3BR Apartment",
        "price": 85000,
        "city": "Nairobi",
        "images": ["https://..."],
        "agent": { "name": "John", "email": "john@example.com", "phone": "..." }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### `GET /api/favorites/:propertyId/status` — Heart Icon State
Used by the property detail page to show filled ❤️ or empty 🤍 on load.

```
GET /api/favorites/684abc123.../status
→ 200  { "success": true, "saved": true }
```

### `DELETE /api/favorites/:propertyId` — Explicit Remove
Direct remove without toggle behaviour — useful for a "Remove" button on the saved listings page.

```
DELETE /api/favorites/684abc123...
→ 200  { "success": true, "saved": false, "message": "Property removed from favorites." }

// If it wasn't saved:
→ 404  { "success": false, "message": "This property is not in your favorites." }
```

