## Edge Cases Handled

| Scenario | What happens |
|---|---|
| Favoriting a non-existent property | 404 — property existence checked first |
| Favoriting same property twice (race condition) | MongoDB duplicate-key error (11000) caught gracefully, returns `saved: true` |
| Fetching favorites when a property was deleted | Filtered out silently — orphaned favorites don't cause errors |
| Unauthenticated request | 401 via `isAuthenticated` middleware |
| Invalid ObjectId format | 400 with clear message |

